The paper introduces a modal logic for expressing properties of computation in the true concurrency setting of stable configuration structures. It focuses on history-preserving bisimulation equivalences and provides logical characterizations of weak history-preserving and history-preserving bisimulation. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories related to logic (cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LOgic) and distributed systems (cs.DS, cs.SE).
